# MCP Tools Specification

DocShark exposes 6 MCP tools following the [Six-Tool Pattern](https://www.mcpbundles.com/blog/mcp-tool-design-pattern) and [MCP best practices](https://www.philschmid.de/mcp-best-practices).

<Callout title="Design intent" label="Agent UX" tone="note">
      The tool set is intentionally narrow. Fewer, purpose-specific tools reduce
      model uncertainty and keep agent behavior predictable across clients.
</Callout>

## Design Principles

1. **Tools are a UI for agents** ‚Äî designed for how an LLM thinks, not a REST API wrapper
2. **Descriptions are everything** ‚Äî the LLM reads descriptions to decide when to use a tool
3. **Pre-processed results** ‚Äî formatted for LLM consumption, not raw data dumps
4. **6 tools max** ‚Äî avoids context rot with clear, non-overlapping purposes
5. **Idempotent reads** ‚Äî search and list operations are safe to retry

## Tool Workflow

```
Agent needs documentation info
         ‚îÇ
         ‚ñº
  ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê
  ‚îÇ list_libraries‚îÇ ‚Üê "What docs are indexed?"
  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò
         ‚îÇ
         ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Library exists ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚Üí search_docs ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚Üí get_doc_page
         ‚îÇ                      (80% of usage)   (deep read)
         ‚îÇ
         ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Not found ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚Üí add_library
                                     ‚îÇ
                               refresh_library  (update)
                                     ‚îÇ
                               remove_library   (cleanup)
```

## search_docs

The primary tool. Full-text search across all indexed documentation.

**When agents use it:** Whenever they need to find information about a library, API, framework feature, or code pattern.

| Parameter | Type   | Required | Description                               |
| --------- | ------ | -------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| `query`   | string | Yes      | Natural language or specific search terms |
| `library` | string | No       | Filter results to a specific library      |
| `limit`   | number | No       | Max results (1-20, default: 5)            |

**Example output:**

```
## Results for "svelte transitions"

### 1. Transitions ‚Äî Svelte 5 Documentation
**Source:** https://svelte.dev/docs/svelte/transition
**Section:** Built-in transitions > fade

Svelte provides several built-in transition functions:
- `fade` ‚Äî fades the element in and out
- `fly` ‚Äî flies the element in from a specified position
```

## list_libraries

Discovery tool. Shows what documentation is currently indexed.

| Parameter | Type   | Required | Description                                      |
| --------- | ------ | -------- | ------------------------------------------------ |
| `status`  | string | No       | Filter: `indexed`, `crawling`, `error`, or `all` |

**Example output:**

```
## Indexed Libraries (4 total)

| Library     | URL                         | Pages | Chunks | Status  |
| ----------- | --------------------------- | ----- | ------ | ------- |
| svelte-5    | https://svelte.dev/docs     | 47    | 312    | indexed |
| tailwind-v4 | https://tailwindcss.com/docs| 89    | 654    | indexed |
```

## get_doc_page

Deep read. Retrieve full markdown content of a specific documentation page.

| Parameter | Type   | Required | Description                        |
| --------- | ------ | -------- | ---------------------------------- |
| `url`     | string | No       | Full URL of the documentation page |
| `library` | string | No       | Library name to search within      |
| `path`    | string | No       | Relative path within the library   |

## add_library

Add a new documentation website to be crawled and indexed.

| Parameter   | Type   | Required | Description                                  |
| ----------- | ------ | -------- | -------------------------------------------- |
| `url`       | string | Yes      | Base URL of the docs site                    |
| `name`      | string | No       | Short identifier (auto-generated if omitted) |
| `version`   | string | No       | Version string (e.g., "5.0.0")               |
| `max_depth` | number | No       | Max crawl depth (1-10, default: 3)           |

## refresh_library

Re-crawl an existing library to get the latest documentation. Only re-fetches pages that have changed via HTTP ETags/Last-Modified.

| Parameter | Type   | Required | Description             |
| --------- | ------ | -------- | ----------------------- |
| `library` | string | Yes      | Library name to refresh |

## remove_library

Permanently remove a documentation library and all its indexed content.

| Parameter | Type   | Required | Description            |
| --------- | ------ | -------- | ---------------------- |
| `library` | string | Yes      | Library name to remove |
